<paragraph blockId="28.[136,1452,1586,2080]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,442,1766,1792]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[442,467,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">—</emphasis>
The species has been collected several times in only one locality in the municipality of Camacan, in the “Reserva Particular do Patrimônio Natural Serra Bonita”. 
<taxonomicName box="[976,1206,1802,1828]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[976,1206,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[1386,1443,1802,1831]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" unit="km" value="3.0">3 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity box="[280,339,1838,1867]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1134,1284,1838,1864]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories.
</paragraph>
