<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[136,1452,1586,2080]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1874,1900]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,529,1874,1900]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[294,529,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[715,783,1874,1900]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation box="[1204,1307,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1262,1307,1874,1900]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers from November to January, and fruits from November to April and June. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,365,1946,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[136,365,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the stem, petioles, leaf blades and hypanthium only glandulose-punctate, leaves with flat surfaces and the suprabasal inner pair of veins, and flowers with white petals and yellow anthers. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,366,2018,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[136,366,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[512,622,2018,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[512,622,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">B. bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For more details see the notes under 
<taxonomicName box="[1049,1159,2018,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[1049,1159,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">B. bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[1195,1404,2018,2045]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[1266,1315,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[136,220,2054,2080]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
